ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4113 Page 1

1 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 26 O.S. 2021, Section 4-101, as
2 amended by Section 1, Chapter 289, O.S.L. 2024 (26 O.S. Supp. 2025,
3 Section 4-101), is amended to read as follows:
4 Section 4-101. Every person who is a qualified elector as
5 defined by Section 1 of Article III of the Oklahoma Constitution
6 shall be entitled to become a registered voter in the precinct of
7 his or her residence, with the following conditions:
8 1. Persons convicted of a felony shall be eligible to register
9 to vote when they have:
10 a. fully served their sentence of court-mandated calendar
11 days or had their sentence discharged, including they
12 have completed any term of incarceration, parole or
13 supervision, or completed a any period of probation
14 ordered by any court for the felony conviction,
15 b. received a commutation that reduced the sentence of
16 any active felony conviction to time served pursuant
17 to federal or state law and have no other outstanding
18 sentence under any other they are not currently on
19 parole, supervision, or probation for the felony
20 conviction, and
21 c. received a commutation pursuant to subsection F of
22 Section 332.2 of Title 57 of the Oklahoma Statutes for
23 a crime that has been reclassified from a felony to a
24
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4113 Page 2

1 misdemeanor and has no remaining time to serve,
2 including:
3 (1) any incomplete term of incarceration,
4 (2) any remaining they are not currently
5 incarcerated, on parole or, on supervision, or
6 (3) any incomplete period of on probation, or
7 d. been granted a pardon pursuant to federal or state law
8 and have no other outstanding sentence under for any
9 other felony conviction; and
10 2. Any person convicted of a felony who has received a
11 commutation or pardon for the felony offense shall be eligible to
12 vote if he or she is not currently incarcerated, on parole, on on
13 supervision, or on probation for another felony conviction; and
14 3. Any person who has been adjudged to be an incapacitated
15 person as such term is defined by Section 1-111 of Title 30 of the
16 Oklahoma Statutes shall be ineligible to register to vote. When
17 such incapacitated person has been adjudged to be no longer
18 incapacitated, such person shall be eligible to become a registered
19 voter. The provisions of this paragraph shall not prohibit any
20 person adjudged to be a partially incapacitated person as such term
21 is defined by Section 1-111 of Title 30 of the Oklahoma Statutes
22 from being eligible to register to vote unless the order adjudging
23 the person to be partially incapacitated restricts such person from
24 being eligible to register to vote.
ENGR. S. A. TO ENGR. H. B. NO. 4113 Page 3

1 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.”
